Well it was one of those - not same as what we've got now - it was a big - big tin one, I can remember that but I can't remember what shape it was
, it must have been shaped like a bath, but we used to - mother used to put the copper on on a Friday night and - I - sister'd have a bath, then I should have her water. Then it would be emptied and then the boys followed on, you know, and - we had to hav
e three lots of water for the six of us, you understand me. Friday. That was the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14766654 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16146915\charrsid12201700 Did the younger children help the older children in any ways?
