We used to have bacon - and I know me mother used to buy those big tins of trantella tomatoes, yo
u know, big ones, and - we always used to have a - a slice of bread dipped into the - gravy, you know, into the juice. And a little bit of bacon on top. That's what we used to have on for our breakfast on Sunday morning and in the - in the week it was mos
tly - bread and dripping or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14766654 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16146915\charrsid12201700 What was the next meal?
