Dinner time. And we used to have - well, me mother used to get - even in those days she used to get these sheeps heads, you know, and - make - and threepennyworth of pot herb
s as she used to call it, carrot and turnip and - parsnip and put it all in and make a - a soup you know, broth, and then she'd cut the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12875267\charrsid12201700 tongue}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16146915\charrsid12201700  out and father'd take that with him for his lunch and we should have the - soup, and she used to cook potatoes se
parate, you know, to it. It was rather nice, it was - cheap, used to get - you could get one in - for about sixpence I think, I know it was a good cheap dinner for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14766654 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16146915\charrsid12201700 Did you have this sort of meal most days?
